---

The terminal — the most stubborn, least-changed tool on the machine, a blinking cursor that's looked the same since the seventies — is quietly turning into something you talk to. You hand it a sentence and it edits the code, runs the tests, reads the errors, tries again. Half a century of muscle memory, and the old black rectangle picked up a brand-new trick. Encouraging, for those of us who've been around almost as long.
